From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 11 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: enable position-independent code globally

Clang static libraries are compiled without -fPIC by default, but
LLVM_BUILD_LLVM_DYLIB=ON causes libclang.so and libclang-cpp.so to be
built from those static library objects. The linker rejects non-PIC
vtable relocations (R_X86_64_PC32) and TLS relocations (R_X86_64_TPOFF32):

  relocation R_X86_64_PC32 against symbol can not be used when making
  a shared object; recompile with -fPIC

Setting CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE globally causes cmake to add
-fPIC to all compilations, making the static library objects safe to
link into shared libraries.
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -1,0 +1,1 @@
+set(CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE ON)
